 and racism, this book explores the nuclear zeitgeist of today. It presents the case for critical nuclear studies, and provides an important intervention into debates about nuclear weapons and international security. Today, the planet stands on the brink of catastrophe. This book tells you why, and what we can do about it.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aNuclear arms control. 0aNuclear warfare. 0aNuclear weapons. 0aSecurity, International. 7aHISTORY / Military / Nuclear Warfare.2bisacsh  aCritical nuclear studies.  aHiroshima.  aINF Treaty.  aNagasaki.  aarms control.  acritical nuclear studies.  acritical security studies.  adeterrence.  adisarmament.  ainternational relations.  ainternational security.  amilitarism.  anuclear disarmament.  anuclear proliferation.  anuclear taboo.  anuclear war.  anuclear weapons.  apopular culture and world politics.  athird nuclear age.1 aCrilley, Rhys, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb40uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152617045340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526170453423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526170453/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles